{"key":"post-11432101","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11432101</id>\n<content>The pH of the salt will kill the mycelium, so scratch that idea.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If your jars are coming out too wet, you need to elevate them off the bottom of the pot during sterilization.&amp;nbsp; I keep the jars totally out of the water so only steam touches them.&amp;nbsp; Between that and being covered with foil during sterilization prevents water from entering the jars.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you're already doing that, you're using too much water when making up the jars.&amp;nbsp; Note that the basic recipe of 1-1-2 counts on using medium to fine verm.&amp;nbsp; If you're using course verm, it holds less water so drop your water content to .8 or so.&amp;nbsp; Also, fine verm makes a better filter.&amp;nbsp; The verm filter should stay dry.&amp;nbsp; Remember, jars made on the dry side colonize much faster.&amp;nbsp; It's better to make dryer jars and then dunk prior to first flush.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11432322</next>\n<prev>11431360</prev>\n<first>11425584</first>\n<last>11432322</last>\n<when>1257959153</when>\n<utime>11/11/09 07:05 PM</utime>\n</post>"}